`= y^2 + 2y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) + (aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ)^2 - aâ‚پxy - aâ‚پ^2x^2 - aâ‚پaâ‚ƒx - aâ‚ƒy - aâ‚پaâ‚ƒx - aâ‚ƒ^2`
`= y^2 + 2y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) + aâ‚پ^2x^2 + 2aâ‚پaâ‚ƒx + aâ‚ƒ^2 - aâ‚پxy - aâ‚پ^2x^2 - 2aâ‚پaâ‚ƒx - aâ‚ƒy - aâ‚ƒ^2`
`= y^2 + 2y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) - aâ‚پxy - aâ‚ƒy`
`= y^2 + y(2aâ‚پx + 2aâ‚ƒ - aâ‚پx - aâ‚ƒ)`
`= y^2 + y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ)`

So we need to show that `y^2 + y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) = x^3 + aâ‚‚x^2 + aâ‚„x + aâ‚†`.

But we know from the original point being on the curve that:
`y^2 + aâ‚پxy + aâ‚ƒy = x^3 + aâ‚‚x^2 + aâ‚„x + aâ‚†`

So, we need to show that `y^2 + y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) = y^2 + aâ‚پxy + aâ‚ƒy`.

Indeed, `y(aâ‚پx + aâ‚ƒ) = y(aâ‚پx) + y(aâ‚ƒ) = aâ‚پxy + aâ‚ƒy`.

So the LHS of the negated point is equal to the RHS of the original equation, which completes the proof.

